declarations.comments: The basic value for a succeeding test.
declarations.title: success

declarations.comments: Make a failing test, given a reason for the failure.
declarations.title: failure

declarations.comments: Set a test to fail after a given number of milliseconds.
declarations.title: timeout

declarations.comments:
Define a test suite, which can contain a number of nested suites
as well as tests.
declarations.title: suite

declarations.comments: Run only this suite.
declarations.title: suiteOnly

declarations.comments: Skip this suite.
declarations.title: suiteSkip

declarations.comments: Define a labelled test.
declarations.title: test

declarations.comments: Run only this test.
declarations.title: testOnly

declarations.comments: Skip a test.
declarations.title: testSkip

declarations.comments:
Filter suites and tests with `Only` and `Skip` flags and removes suites
that do not contain any tests.
declarations.title: filterTests

declarations.comments:
A list of collected tests, represented as a tuple of each test's path
and the `Test` itself. The path, in this case, means the name of the
test preceded by the name of each parent test suite, in top down order.
declarations.title: TestList

declarations.comments:
Walk through a test suite, calling the provided function for each item,
and returning a `TestList` of all tests walked. The tests won't actually
run unless you run them explicitly from your walker function.
declarations.title: walkSuite

declarations.comments:
Walk through a test suite, returning a `TestList` of all tests walked.
This operation will not actually run the tests.
declarations.title: collectTests

declarations.comments: Run a list of tests and collect each test result.
declarations.title: collectResults

declarations.comments: Filter successes out of a list of test results.
declarations.title: keepErrors

declarations.comments: `describe` is an alias for `suite` for BDD enthusiasts.
declarations.title: describe

declarations.comments: `it` is an alias for `test` for BDD enthusiasts.
declarations.title: it

declarations.comments:
Given a failure reason and a boolean, either succeed if the boolean is
true, or fail if the boolean is false.
declarations.title: assert

declarations.comments:
The reverse of `assert`: given a failure reason and a boolean, either
succeed if the boolean is false, or fail if the boolean is true.
declarations.title: assertFalse

declarations.comments:
Expect a test to fail. Given a reason and a test, fail with the given
reason if the test succeeds, and succeed if it fails.
declarations.title: expectFailure

declarations.comments: Assert that two printable values are equal.
declarations.title: equal

declarations.comments:
Assert that two non-printable values are equal, using a provided failure
string instead of generating one.
declarations.title: equal'

declarations.comments:
`shouldEqual` is equivalent to `equal`, with the arguments flipped,
for people who prefer the BDD style.

    it "should do what I expect of it" do
      result `shouldEqual` "expected result"
declarations.title: shouldEqual

declarations.comments:
Exit the current process using the provided return code.

Works on Node and Phantom. Will have no effect on other platforms.
declarations.title: exit

declarations.comments: Run a test suite using the provided test runner.
declarations.title: runTestWith

declarations.comments: Run a test suite, picking the most appropriate test runner.
declarations.title: runTest
